"adv.并列，并排 【英】 并列,并排(side by side);跟上某事物( remain up to date with sth.) 【记】 a+breast(胸) →胸和胸并排 【例】 keep abreast of current affairs adv. 并肩地, 并排地 【例】to march abreast 并肩前进You should keep abreast with the science 你们应当赶上科学的发展. 【记】a一对, breast乳房―并排地 【记】a + breast 并胸，运动员赛跑时胸是并排的 abreast (adv.)  mid-15c., on brest, from a- (1) + breast (n.); the notion is of ""with breasts in line."" To keep abreast in figurative sense of ""stay up-to-date"" is from 1650s."
